Overview
This repository contains the code and resources for a movie genre classification system. The goal of this project is to develop a machine learning model that can automatically classify movies into predefined genres based on their textual descriptions or other relevant features.

Introduction
Movie genre classification is a fundamental task in the field of natural language processing and machine learning. It has various applications, including recommendation systems, content tagging, and search optimization. This project aims to build a robust movie genre classification model using state-of-the-art techniques.

Requirements
Before running the project, ensure you have the following dependencies installed

Python 3.x
Pandas
NumPy
Seaborn
Matplotlib
NLTK
Scikit-learn
